Rivers State Governor, Nyesom Wike, on Tuesday, received the All Progressive Congress, (APC) Presidential Candidate, President Muhammadu Buhari at the Nigeria Air Base airstrip in Port Harcourt. Governor Wike, who is a Peoples Democratic Party chieftain, and some members of the State Executive Council welcomed the President at about 10.17 am. The Rivers State Governor presented a bouquet of flowers to the President. The President boarded a Nigerian Air Force helicopter and left to Bayelsa State for Campaigns and he is being expected back at Port Harcourt to attend another Presidential campaign at Adoki Amasiemeka Stadium. PHOTOS: Wike welcomes Buhari who commissioned Port Harcourt Airport terminal Buhari commissions Port Harcourt International Airport Terminal Saraki visits Rivers, says he has capacity to revive Nigeria